    <article class="recipe">
        <h1>Grilled Stuffed Peppers with Couscous</h1>

        
        
        <span class="published"><span class="value-title" title="2010-01-08"></span></span>
        
        
                            
      
        
        <h3 class="recipe_source">
            
                <a href="http://www.womansday.com/" target="_blank">Woman's Day</a>
            
        </h3>
                            



        


        
        <figure class="recipeimg">
        <img src="/cm/womansday/images/hG/Grilled-Stuffed-Peppers-with-Couscous-Recipe-lg.jpg" />
            <figcaption>Charles Schiller</figcaption>
        </figure>
        

        <h2 class="deck"><span class="summary">Brightly colored peppers not only make a bold statement on the table, but they&#146;re a delicious way to serve up a Moroccan-tinged mix of couscous, currants, tomato, feta, almonds and spices.</span></h2>
        <p class="byline">By <span class="author">Woman's Day Kitchen </span></p>
    
        <section class="yield">
              
            <p class="duration">
                
                40 min
                <!--<span class="value-title" title="PT
                40M"></span> -->                       
            </p>
            <p class="preptime">
                
                20 min
                <!--<span class="value-title" title="PT
                20M"></span> -->                       
            </p>
            
            
        </section>


        <section class="recipeingredients">
                
                
                
                <p class="ingredient">
                    2
                    cup(s)
                    
                    chicken broth 
                </p>
                
                <p class="ingredient">
                    3
                    tablespoon(s)
                    
                    extra-virgin olive oil 
                </p>
                
                <p class="ingredient">
                    2
                    clove(s)
                    
                    garlic, finely chopped
                </p>
                
                <p class="ingredient">
                    0.25
                    teaspoon(s)
                    
                    salt 
                </p>
                
                <p class="ingredient">
                    2
                    cup(s)
                    
                    whole-wheat, tomato or regular couscous
                </p>
                
                <p class="ingredient">
                    0.333333333333
                    cup(s)
                    
                    dried currants 
                </p>
                
                <p class="ingredient">
                    1
                    large
                    
                    tomato, diced
                </p>
                
                <p class="ingredient">
                    12
                    ounce(s)
                    
                    fresh feta cheese, crumbled
                </p>
                
                <p class="ingredient">
                    4
                    
                    
                    scallions, thinly sliced
                </p>
                
                <p class="ingredient">
                    0.5
                    cup(s)
                    
                    chopped, toasted almonds
                </p>
                
                <p class="ingredient">
                    0.333333333333
                    cup(s)
                    
                    chopped fresh mint 
                </p>
                
                <p class="ingredient">
                    1
                    tablespoon(s)
                    
                    chopped fresh oregano 
                </p>
                
                <p class="ingredient">
                    0.5
                    teaspoon(s)
                    
                    freshly ground pepper 
                </p>
                
                <p class="ingredient">
                    6
                    large
                    
                    mixed peppers (red, orange, green, purple and/or yellow)
                </p>
                
                <p class="ingredient">
                    
                    
                    
                    Olive oil cooking spray 
                </p>
                
                <p class="ingredient">
                    
                    
                    
                    Serve with: lemon wedges and extra-virgin olive oil for drizzling 
                </p>
                
                
                
                
        </section>



        
        <ul class="nutritional_info">
            <lh>Nutritional Information <span>(per serving)</span></lh>
            <li class="calories">
                <strong>254</strong>
            </li>
            <li class="total_fat">
                13g
            </li>
            <li class="saturated_fat">
                5g
            </li>
            <li class="cholesterol">
                25mg
            </li>
            <li class="sodium">
                533mg
            </li>
            <li class="total_carbohydrates">
                27g
            </li>
            <li class="fiber">
                5g
            </li>
            <li class="sugar">
                n/a
            </li>
            <li class="protein">
                9g
            </li>
            <li class="calcium">
                --
            </li>
        </ul>

        
        <section class="directions">
                <ol class="directions instructions">
                
                    
                    <li><span>Bring broth, 1 Tbsp oil, the garlic and salt to a boil in a large saucepan. Stir in couscous and currants, remove from heat, cover and let stand 5 minutes or until broth is absorbed.</span></li>
                    <li><span>Transfer to a large bowl; fluff with a fork. Let cool 5 minutes. Stir in remaining 2 Tbsp oil and the remaining Filling ingredients.</span></li>
                    <li><span>While Filling cools, cut peppers in half lengthwise through stems; remove seeds and membranes, keeping stems intact. Cut a thin slice off rounded sides of each half so they won't wobble; coat rounded sides with cooking spray. Put cut sides up on baking sheet.</span></li>
                    <li><span>Heat grill. Fill peppers with Filling. Place directly on grill rack, cover grill and cook 12 to 15 minutes until peppers are tender and bottoms are charred in spots. Serve hot or at room temperature.</span></li>                     
                
                </ol>
                
                <!--concordance-end-->
                
                
                   
        </section>
    </article>


            
			
			
            
            
            
            

            
            
            
            
            
            
            
            
            
            

			
            
            
        
			


